Hot is the debut album by British pop singer Melanie B , released on 9 October 2000 by Virgin .
The album was not as successful as her albums with the Spice Girls or that of other members solo albums released around this time .
It peaked at number twenty-eight in United Kingdom and sold over 60,000 copies , receiving a silver certification .
The album had four singles : `` I Want You Back '' , featuring Missy Elliott , `` Tell Me '' , `` Feels So Good '' and `` Lullaby '' .
The first three singles reached top 5 in United Kingdom .
The single `` Word Up '' , previously released on the soundtrack of the film Austin Powers : The Spy Who Shagged Me , was included on the Japanese version .
The album received mixed to negative reviews from critics .